Here are 20 additional metrics to consider for your monitoring dashboard:

Access & Governance
Privilege grants per day — sudden spikes in GRANTS_TO_ROLES or GRANTS_TO_USERS may indicate unauthorized access expansion
Roles with ACCOUNTADMIN usage — track how often ACCOUNTADMIN is actively used vs. delegated roles (QUERY_HISTORY filtered by role)
Masking policy invocations — how often masked columns are queried, and by whom (POLICY_REFERENCES + ACCESS_HISTORY)
Row access policy denials — queries silently returning fewer rows than expected due to RLS
Unused roles — roles granted but never assumed in 90+ days (LOGIN_HISTORY cross-referenced with GRANTS_TO_USERS)
Data Movement & Integration
External function latency — response time of external API integrations (EXTERNAL_FUNCTIONS_HISTORY)
Data sharing consumption — how much shared data is being queried by consumers (DATA_TRANSFER_HISTORY)
Snowpipe file notification lag — time between file arrival and load completion (COPY_HISTORY)
Cross-region data transfer volume — GB transferred between regions, billed separately (DATA_TRANSFER_HISTORY)
Materialized view maintenance credits — hidden cost of keeping MVs refreshed (MATERIALIZED_VIEW_REFRESH_HISTORY)
Efficiency & Waste
Warehouse auto-suspend effectiveness — average time from last query to suspend (WAREHOUSE_EVENTS_HISTORY). Your WH_TRXS_TRANSFORM may benefit from a tighter suspend policy
Repeat/duplicate queries — identical query hashes run multiple times, suggesting missing caching or redundant pipelines (QUERY_HISTORY grouped by QUERY_PARAMETERIZED_HASH)
Queries scanning >80% of table partitions — full table scans that should be optimized (QUERY_HISTORY with PARTITIONS_SCANNED/PARTITIONS_TOTAL > 0.8)
Remote spilling ratio — remote spills are far more expensive than local; track BYTES_SPILLED_TO_REMOTE_STORAGE separately
Result cache hit rate — percentage of queries served from cache without warehouse spin-up (QUERY_HISTORY where BYTES_SCANNED = 0 and results returned)
Operational Reliability
Schema change frequency — DDL operations on production schemas, detecting unplanned changes (QUERY_HISTORY filtered by QUERY_TYPE IN ('CREATE_TABLE', 'ALTER_TABLE', 'DROP_TABLE'))
Long-running queries (>5 min) — count per day, trend over time, which users/warehouses
Concurrent query peaks — max simultaneous queries per warehouse per hour, to right-size multi-cluster configs
Network policy violations — blocked connection attempts from disallowed IPs (LOGIN_HISTORY with IS_SUCCESS = 'NO' and ERROR_MESSAGE LIKE '%network%')
Object dependency depth — views built on views built on views; deep chains are fragile and slow (OBJECT_DEPENDENCIES)
